Burberry Group plc Key Developments

Burberry Group plc Appoints Marco Gobbetti as Director
Jul 14 17
Burberry Group plc has appointed Marco Gobbetti as a Director. The effective date is July 13, 2017.


Burberry Group PLC Approves Dividend for the Year Ended March 31, 2017
Jul 13 17
Burberry Group PLC at its AGM held on July 13, 2017 declared a final dividend of 28.4 pence per ordinary share for the year ended March 31, 2017.


Burberry Group plc Announces Revenue Results for the First Quarter Ended June 30, 2017; Provides Revenue Guidance for the Second Half of Fiscal Year 2018 and Earnings Guidance for the Fiscal Year 2018
Jul 12 17
Burberry Group plc announced revenue results for the first quarter ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, retail revenue was £478 million, up 3% underlying (up 13% at reported FX). Comparable sales were up 4%. 


For the second half of fiscal year 2018, the company currently expects underlying wholesale revenue, excluding Beauty, to be down due to brand control. 

For the fiscal year 2018, the company expects total underlying licensing revenue for fiscal year 2018 is still expected to be up c.20% year-on-year including the impact of Beauty. Guidance for fiscal year 2018 adjusted PBT at constant exchange rates is maintained. At 30 June effective rates, the expected impact of year-on-year exchange rate movements on fiscal year 2018 reported adjusted PBT is around £25 million adverse compared to previous guidance for £30 million adverse at 28 April effective rates.


